  "notes": "The 2UZ-FE is Toyota's 4.7L all-aluminum DOHC V8, produced from 1998 to 2011. It is widely regarded as one of Toyota's most reliable V8 engines. Compression ratio is 9.6:1 on earlier models and 10.0:1 on VVT-i variants introduced around 2005. The VVT-i version (post-2005 Land Cruiser 100, Lexus LX470 from 2005) produces slightly more power. The \"2UZ swap\" into the 80-series Land Cruiser is a well-documented and popular build, often using donor engines from wrecked 100-series Land Cruisers or Lexus LX470s. The all-aluminum construction keeps weight competitive despite displacement. Compatible bellhousing pattern with the 3UZ-FE (Lexus SC430/GS430) allows 3UZ transmissions in some builds.",
